    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini Dei aeterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/79"
                            >Hugo</persName> et <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/72"
                            >Lotharius</persName> divina providente clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">reges</rs>. Regalem decet exellentiam iustis
                        fidelium petitionibus adsensum prebere. Quocirca omnium fidelium sanctae Dei
                        Ecclesie nostrorumque presentium ac futurorum devotio noverit, qualiter <rs
                            key="#Intercessory">interventu ac petitione</rs>
                        <persName key="#Intercessory #Count #fidelisOf"><name ref="Ildericus"
                                >Ilderici</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs> dilectique <rs key="#fidelisOf">fidelis</rs>
                        nostri,, prout iuste et legaliter possumus, per hoc nostre confirmationis
                        preceptum confirmamus ac corroboramus <persName key="#fidelisOf"><name
                                ref="Bernardus">Bernardo</name></persName> nostri <rs
                            key="#fidelisOf">fideli</rs> omnes res proprietatis sue iuste et
                        legaliter adquisitas et adquirendas, sive familias emptionis commutationis
                        vel quolibet titulo legalis scriptionis sibi pertinentes: res in <rs
                            key="#Casalia">casale</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Casalia #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            ref="#estates/2384">Manditiano</geogName>, in <placeName
                            ref="#places/2778">Campriano</placeName> et <placeName
                            ref="#places/2777">Blatiano</placeName>, vel per singula loca et
                        vocabula regni nostri adiacentes; recipientes eundem Bernardum et <rs
                            key="#childOf">filios suos</rs> sub nostre <rs
                            key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">tuitionis mundburdum</rs> una cum
                        omnibus rebus mobilibus et immobilibus sibi iuste et legaliter
                        pertinentibus, <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis et ancillis</rs>. Precipientes
                        itaque iubemus, ut nullus dux, marchio, comes, vicecomes, seu quelibet regni
                        nostri magna parvaque persona predictum Bernardum molestare vel de suis
                        rebus desvestire audeat, absque legali iuditio. Si quis igitur huius nostri
                        precepti confirmationem seu mundburdi tuitionem aliquando infringere conatus
                        fuerit, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras
                            quinquaginta</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem kamere nostre</rs>
                        et <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem prefato
                            [Be]rnardo suisque heredibus</rs>. Quod ut verius credatur
                        diligentiusque ab omnibus observetur, manibus pro[p]riis roborantes anulo
                        nostro insigniri iussimus. Signa serenissimorum (MF) (MF) Hugonis et
                        Lotharii regum. <persName key="#Chancellor" ref="#people/1535"
                            >Giseprandus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/1531">Bosonis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovi et subscripsi (SR) (SID). Data XII kal.
                        novembris, anno dominice incarnationis DCCCCXLIII, regni vero domni Hugonis
                        XVIII, Lotharii XIII, indictione secunda. Actum <placeName ref="#places/65"
                            >Papie</placeName>, feliciter.</ab>
                </div>
